INSERT INTO `user_thanks` VALUES (2,3,'Pat McManus',1,'Madhu','msprabhakara@gmail.com','','Thanks for just being you buddy!','For just being you, Madhu, Thank you.','2017-08-15 22:52:53','2017-08-15 23:12:05'),(3,43,'Janani',1,'Madhu Prabhakara','msprabhakara@gmail.com',NULL,'Test','Test','2017-08-15 22:53:53','2017-09-20 15:18:23'),(5,5,'Sandra Muriel',3,'Pat McManus','mcmanupe@gmail.com','','Great team work!','Thanks for everything!','2017-08-16 22:20:23','2017-08-16 22:20:23'),(6,3,'Pat McManus',5,'Sandra Muriel','samupri87@hotmail.com','','Right back at ya!','Thank YOU Sandra! Great working with you. And sweet picture from Yosemite.','2017-08-16 22:33:24','2017-08-16 22:33:24'),(9,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Babs','babs_olaniran@yahoo.com','','The believer!','I have absolutely no words for this great person who is my classmate and my friend. We had an idea that we are working on. Many said the idea is good and has a good social cause but Babs was the only person who said I like the idea and here is my money. Go build it. Thanks a lot Babs for believing in us not just with words but with your money.','2017-08-17 17:23:18','2017-08-17 17:23:18'),(10,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',39,'Reem','reem.fatayri@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/683b62c741b1bb5070a268a6be7a59b6.jpeg','Module A Team 2 - The Best!','The best team I ever worked for and I  if I ever get a chance to work for this team again, I will gladly do. Thanks Reem, Cynthia, Pat, Eve, Sergey for showing what its like to be working in such teams. Did we have strict rules, NO. Did we have a team charter that we followed religiously, NO.  Did we come out satisfied with our work, YES! Did we win the 3 bottles of wine, hell YES!  Team is a team, fail together and win together!','2017-08-17 19:12:15','2017-08-30 19:56:52'),(11,2,'Kailash Suresh',0,'Sarah Scholl','sarah-leigh@msn.com','','For all the good times!','Thanks for being a super awesome friend through this year. !','2017-08-17 21:26:16','2017-08-17 21:26:16'),(12,2,'Kailash Suresh',13,'Giulia','giulia.belloni@yahoo.it','','For all the good times!','For all the good times and great conversations we have had!','2017-08-17 21:33:30','2017-08-18 21:54:31'),(13,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',3,'Pat McManus','mcmanupe@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/683b62c741b1bb5070a268a6be7a59b6.jpeg','Module A Team 2 - The Best!','The best team I ever worked for and I if I ever get a chance to work for this team again, I will gladly do. Thanks Reem, Cynthia, Pat, Eve, Sergey for showing what its like to be working in such teams. Did we have strict rules, NO. Did we have a team charter that we followed religiously, NO. Did we come out satisfied with our work, YES! Did we win the 3 bottles of wine, hell YES! Team is a team, fail together and win together!.','2017-08-17 22:01:42','2017-08-17 22:01:42'),(14,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Taylor Otwell','taylor@laravel.com','','Dedicated to the open source community','I have always wondered why do people create world class products and give it away for free?? Today, instead of focusing on the why I would like to thank \"Taylor Otwell\" for creating a world class product called Laravel, a PHP framework. Mr Taylor, if it makes you happy, you should know \"thankingli\" is proudly powered by Laravel!! Thank you so much.','2017-08-18 02:34:19','2017-08-18 02:34:19'),(15,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',36,'Ray DeRenzo','raderenzo@gmail.com','','Thanks for being selfless','Ray, I just wanted to thank you for all the time and the help you extended during our ideation phase of Walleee.  You selflessly gave us your time and helped us in reaching a stage where we started liking the idea even more. It meant a lot to us. Thank you!','2017-08-18 05:24:06','2017-08-28 19:22:35'),(16,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Jeffrey Way','jeffrey@laracasts.com','','For the splendid Laravel lessons','Jeffrey, Thanks a lot for the awesome laravel training material that you\'ve put up on Laracasts. \"Thankingli\" is proudly powered by laravel! People like you definitely make this world a better place.','2017-08-18 05:29:06','2017-08-18 05:29:06'),(17,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',5,'Sandra Muriel','samupri87@hotmail.com','','for friendship and for being so selfless!','Thank you so much Sandra for selflessly helping me in improving this. Your feedback has been invaluable. It is these similar events that have led me to start building this platform. Thank you!','2017-08-19 05:45:42','2017-08-19 05:45:42'),(19,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',14,'Prasad','prasi55@gmail.com','','To my friend and my mentor','Thank you Prasad for the friendship and the mentorship. I believe I met you at the right time in my life when I needed someone to encourage me and guide me. I probably would\'ve quit but universe has strange ways and I met you. We will do the iron man some day! A big Thank you for everything!.','2017-08-19 14:50:51','2017-08-19 19:29:54'),(20,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Daniel Morgan','morgandaniel@hgcbroadband.com','','One of the best people I worked for','My resume looks more glittering because of you Daniel. I am able to talk about my accomplishments because you once believed in me and encouraged me. Thank you so much Daniel!','2017-08-19 17:13:34','2017-08-19 17:13:34'),(21,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',34,'Sinthia Rojas','Rojasgeldres.sc@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/683b62c741b1bb5070a268a6be7a59b6.jpeg','Module A Team 2 - The Best!','The best team I ever worked for and I if I ever get a chance to work for this team again, I will gladly do. Thanks Reem, Cynthia, Pat, Eve, Sergey for showing what its like to be working in such teams. Did we have strict rules, NO. Did we have a team charter that we followed religiously, NO. Did we come out satisfied with our work, YES! Did we win the 3 bottles of wine, hell YES! Team is a team, fail together and win together!','2017-08-19 18:22:15','2017-08-27 19:41:54'),(22,15,'Ruslana',2,'Kailash Suresh','kailash.suresh@gmail.com','','Tennis class ?','Thank you for an awesome tennis class ! I had a lot of fun playing with you :)','2017-08-19 22:22:21','2017-08-19 22:22:21'),(23,2,'Kailash Suresh',16,'Rodica','rodica.lupu.office@gmail.com','','Thank u for saloon!','Thank you for the great selection. Awesome evening.','2017-08-20 05:46:39','2017-08-20 17:56:43'),(24,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Everado','evetopete_89@hotmail.com','thankingli-images/1/683b62c741b1bb5070a268a6be7a59b6.jpeg','Module A Team 2 - The Best!','The best team I ever worked for and I  if I ever get a chance to work for this team again, I will gladly do. Thanks Reem, Cynthia, Pat, Eve, Sergey for showing what its like to be working in such teams. Did we have strict rules, NO. Did we have a team charter that we followed religiously, NO.  Did we come out satisfied with our work, YES! Did we win the 3 bottles of wine, hell YES!  Team is a team, fail together and win together!','2017-08-20 06:03:56','2017-08-20 06:03:56'),(25,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',17,'Sumana','sumanasamuk@gmail.com','','For being a friend and for being strong!','Thanks Som for being a wonderful person, for keeping in touch  and for staying strong. I have no doubt that you will be successful no matter what you wish to do in this life.','2017-08-21 00:20:36','2017-08-21 00:42:56'),(29,19,'Sidharth Vijayan',44,'Maïté Chennangattu','chennmai@gmail.com','thankingli-images/19/b1097b8e55fc3f722caff7a7231621ce.jpeg','Strength & Grace','Dear Maité, \r\n       I have known you for a little less than a year now and I must say you are one of the strongest woman I have crossed path with. You are humble and soft at the same time, you can be strong and assertive when the time comes. I\'m proud to be a friend of such a strong, humble and understanding person. Wish you all the very best in life... \r\nSid...','2017-08-24 01:10:19','2017-09-21 22:44:09'),(30,19,'Sidharth Vijayan',1,'Madhu Prabhakara','masprabhakara@gmail.com','thankingli-images/19/ffcc11f4a19755ac38140e8fbae16aa6.png','A Friend For Life','Dear Madhu, \r\nwe met almost a year ago at a leadership class and we seem to have hit it off right there as great buddies with similar ideologies and goals in mind. You have taught me to stay calm through adversity during these last few months and helped me stay grounded when I\'ve gone crazy with situations that didn\'t seem favorable to me. You truly have been a brother from another mother... \r\nRegards,\r\nSid...','2017-08-24 01:34:32','2017-08-24 01:34:32'),(31,19,'Sidharth Vijayan',21,'Vivek Vijay Surve','viveksurve@ymail.com','thankingli-images/19/7688fd292c449cfad896ddcf688c8175.jpeg','Vivek - Thank You!','Hult may have got us to meet, but it is your humble nature and grit towards making a better life that made me want to be great friends with you. Keep the positive vibes and see yourself grow to heights you have never imagined. Thank you for inspiring me to be the best version of myself with health. \r\nSid...','2017-08-24 01:58:31','2017-08-24 01:58:31'),(32,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',21,'Vivek Surve','vivek@sopact.com','thankingli-images/1/e71eda7893f916763c6d1319706b34d8.png','To my Bhau','Vivek Bhau(means brother in marathi, an indian language), I just wanted to thank you for being an inspiration to me, for encouraging me to get fitter and to follow a healthy diet. If you want to get fitter and can show dedication, Vivek will not only train you, but ensure that you stay focussed on your goals. Simply put, he would just be there for you. All this without any ulterior motive other than to see you succeed. Thanks for being such a wonderful friend and a person.','2017-08-24 02:32:44','2017-08-24 02:32:44'),(33,28,'Shivangi Vyasulu',2,'Kailash Suresh','kailash.suresh@gmail.com',NULL,'For the Music','Thank you for being a part of so many wonderful live music memories!','2017-08-24 18:53:38','2017-08-24 18:53:38'),(34,29,'Ahmad Qatamesh',33,'Rosey Singh','singh.rosey@gmail.com',NULL,'Everything you done or said for me','Huge emotional support and insights, she is my best friend and asset, and help me feel involved whenever i felt alone, can\'t thank you enough','2017-08-24 19:14:47','2017-08-27 18:54:42'),(36,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',19,'Sidharth Vijayan','sidhboss@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/07aa282724994a365af7d7469ec2e25f.jpeg','To my friend, my brother','Thank you so much for the friendship, for the partnership and for everything in between. You gave me the courage to go beyond having ideas in my head. You brought out the entrepreneur in me. This wouldn\'t have been possible without the endless drawing board discussions and of course the arguments we\'ve had. I am excited to find out what we accomplish together!','2017-08-25 00:26:51','2017-08-25 00:26:51'),(37,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',32,'Harshith Dayanand','harsh.md@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/65ee58c9e40fa7b18120b19268257060.jpeg','Miss our days in bangalore!','The long coffee breaks, the extended lunch breaks, the long conversations in the meeting rooms. Never have I enjoyed my life as I did with you, Vijay and Satheesh. Thanks a lot for the friendship Harshith!','2017-08-25 04:39:46','2017-08-25 04:39:46'),(38,19,'Sidharth Vijayan',21,'Vivek Surve','vivek@sopact.com','thankingli-images/19/0cbb57cff75b93c015a3ba2f0d31121d.jpeg','Pure Positivity','My friend, you are something else when it comes to being positive in life. Your intent to help others is just pure positivity and contagious. I know you will do great in life and hope that I can be of some help to you sometime soon. Thank you for all the help you have extended through our journey during our MBA at Hult. You are a star!','2017-08-25 19:12:09','2017-08-25 19:12:09'),(39,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',38,'Vijay Suthanthira','vij.rules@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/c49542b2797e7140580d123e480636cb.jpeg','Inspirational Co-worker and now a great friend','Vijay was my senior at Cisco systems and what ever I did and learned in close to 6.5 years at Cisco, he has been a major part of that. You need your seniors to support you at your work for you to be effective, Vijay went beyond that. He was a senior who treated me like a friend, a reason I believe led to all the innovative work we did. Proud to have collaborated with you on MESH/HEX and iSMS, we changed the way people thought about system engineering. Thanks for the inspiration  Vijay!','2017-08-30 00:03:18','2017-08-30 11:33:29'),(40,37,'Shrikant Tiwari',2,'Kailash Suresh','kailash.suresh@gmail.com','thankingli-images/37/11a5b751984462d50fd5b25c0bbdfb1f.jpeg','For being there','Kailash, I really don\'t remember the first time we met. My memory is horrible that way. But I do remember our trip back from Chennai and that crazy video we took on the platform. From then on you have annoyed me to no end, from small things like forgetting your class schedule to big ones that I won\'t mention. I wouldn\'t have it any other way. you may annoy me like hell but you will always remain a true friend to me for a long time. Thank you, my friend.','2017-08-30 06:23:28','2017-08-30 06:23:28'),(41,37,'Shrikant Tiwari',17,'Sumana Samuk','sumanasamuk@gmail.com','thankingli-images/37/4458d736febac6364fe985d8f7dc64a7.jpeg','For everything','So I wrote a long emotionally draining note here only to be told that it can\'t exceed 500 words. so here is the short version. Su, thank you for being family, thank you for being the person who reminds me of who I am and where I come from. Thank you for keeping me grounded and for a million other things that I have no space to write about. Thank you, Su. p.s I did not buy fluffy. :D','2017-08-30 06:53:03','2017-08-30 06:53:03'),(42,37,'Shrikant Tiwari',0,'Nikhil Hiremath','nikkspeed@yahoo.co.in','thankingli-images/37/79e5ad8da3d0d6794ac00c6e59ee8382.jpeg','NA','The title is NA coz I really didn\'t know what to put in there. Nikhil. They say rishte khoon se nahi bante and I believe that saying. if I didn\'t then I would not consider you my brother. When you said you were proud of me I felt elated. If I start thanking you chronologically, this website will crash so I will just say this: salute mi Familia. thank you my brother.  ps sorry about the pic','2017-08-30 07:09:59','2017-08-30 07:09:59'),(43,38,'VIJAY',1,'Madhu Prabhakara','msprabhakara@gmail.com',NULL,'Friend for Life!','Hi Madhukar, \r\nFirst of all, Congratulations on the launch of thankingli. What was your dream a while ago, has now become a reality. I couldn\'t be happier! Well, thats not true. I\'ll be happier when this platform takes off and reaches its true purpose and potential. I\'ll be even more happier when you share the news that there are many new ventures that you\'re getting involved with or initiating. All the very best maga! \r\n\r\nYou are definitely one of the most sincere and honest people that I\'ve met. It was such fun working with you on MESH/HEX/iSMS. Those were really good days and sleepless nights and I loved every second of it, all the discussions, learnings, arguments, disagreements, and the final implementation. Over the course of knowing you, there\'s so much I\'ve learnt techincally and most importantly, about what kind of a person you are as well. Needless to say, it has certainly left a positive impact in my life and my thinking. You are one of my best friends Madhukar! Thank you.\r\n\r\nKeep rocking maga! I sincerely wish you all the success that you truly deserve. \r\n\r\nThanks\r\nVijay','2017-09-02 02:54:26','2017-09-02 02:54:26'),(44,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',42,'Brett Noyes','brnoyes@unbankventures.com',NULL,'For believing in us','From our first meeting where we spoke about the hardware we wanted to make to Walleee in its current form where it evolved into a e-commerce platform, the one thing that has been a constant has been your support to us and our ideas. You have genuinely been an awesome person. Thanks a lot Brett for believing in us and for giving us opportunities to make things happen. This means a lot!','2017-09-03 05:27:02','2017-09-19 16:35:36'),(45,40,'Ange',0,'Leon De-Levi','ldelevi@pacunion.com','thankingli-images/40/62674631d341d6cef8813c40e813aad8.png','You\'re effin awesome!','You saved my life, in more ways than one. \r\nYou brought me back to me. To you. To Life. To Success. To the Universe.\r\nYou believe in me. \r\nThank you.\r\nI am grateful for you. You push me. You inspire me. You genuinely love me.\r\nWe are fit for one another.\r\nMy success is your success and vice versa.\r\nMy heart skips a beat... \r\n\r\nThank you, love of mine. \r\n\r\nYou are everything. <3','2017-09-08 05:47:39','2017-09-08 05:47:39'),(46,37,'Shrikant Tiwari',21,'Vivek Surve','vivek@sopact.com',NULL,'Thank You','Vivek, \r\nWhen I met my parents at the airport before graduation, they couldn\'t recognize me. They could not believe how much weight I had lost. Every gram of that weight I lost was because you kept me motivated, you kept encouraging me. Thank you for doing that. More than that you have been an amazing friend to me and I will always remember our movie nights. \r\nThank you.','2017-09-09 01:06:23','2017-09-09 01:06:23'),(51,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Software community around the world',NULL,'thankingli-images/1/77d1eb970da5137494e0fc97fef00ab6.jpeg','Thanks to the software community: anyone can build an amazing application for free!','I have always wondered why people create wonderful products and literally give them out for free. Many great applications in the world have been created using these free tools. \r\n\r\nI just wanted to tell everybody, how people can, with a little effort and learning, literally build any internet product and it won’t cost them a dime. What more, you can put it out there in front of the world without having to spend any money. Isn’t this wonderful??\r\n\r\nHaving had the opportunity and the privilege of using some of these products, I would like to offer my deepest gratitude and appreciation for those who have built and released world class products. The world is definitely a better place because of these people.\r\n\r\nTaylor Otwell for Laravel - A fabulous PHP framework for web development \r\n\r\nRasmus Lerdorf for PHP - It is impossible to count the number of websites that are powered by this language\r\n\r\nAlgolia - for the splendid search functionality. this is free for community plans.\r\n\r\nJeff Bezos for AWS - One of the best innovations of our times, You could literally host your web platform for free for an entire year and it offers ton of other features which can mostly be used for free!\r\n\r\nSergey and Larry for Google analytics - You should use this to really know how powerful it is!\r\n\r\nTo all my friends and to the people who will become my friends, I know how daunting the task may seem to build something technical, it may seem impossible in the beginning but you can. You are not alone, there is a lot of help around you. Please do not hesitate to message me; I can help people to get started - of course for free!','2017-09-15 06:37:24','2017-09-15 06:37:24'),(52,19,'Sidharth Vijayan',49,'Barista at Tazza D’More 4th & King SFO','tazzadamore@gmail.com',NULL,'Anyone can make your day. Thank you dear random barista...','It is rare that you have a cappuccino and find it to be better than all the other coffees you may have had in the past. Today was one such day where the barista whipped me the best cappuccino ever.... When you are about to embark on a long train journey alone, you could do with all the positive vibes you get and they can come in all shapes, sizes and forms. Mine came today in the form a positive smiling person who made one of the best coffees I’ve had In a while. Thank you for making my day.....\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nSid...','2017-09-26 02:27:46','2017-10-03 18:33:43'),(53,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',0,'Howard',NULL,'thankingli-images/1/37da8f759201ca2236c38e357338c467.jpeg','We can learn from anyone, because the world is our teacher!','What would have costed us $27800 costed us $25000, saving us $2800.\r\n\r\nThis happened a year ago. My wife and I came out of a car dealership and got into an Uber. \r\n\r\nThe driver welcomed us with a warm smile and asked us if we dropped off our car for service. We said no and I hesitatingly told him that we were there to buy a car. This was our first experience trying to buy a car in the US and honestly we were clueless. \r\n\r\nThe next 10 minutes of this conversation completely changed the way we were going about the whole process. \r\n\r\nHoward(the Uber driver) asked us if we were paying by cash or would it be a loan. We said it would be a combination. Some in down payment and the rest in loan. Then he asked us if we were already approved for the loan by any bank. My thoughts at this point were why is he asking is so many questions and that too on a topic that people wouldn’t be very comfortable revealing that too to a stranger. \r\n\r\nI don\'t know what happened but I decided to take the conversation forward, and I don\'t regret my decision.\r\n\r\nI told Howard that we thought of negotiating for a price and then getting the loan approved. \r\n\r\nHe then told us, how, with our approach, there is a chance that we’d end up NOT on the better side of the deal. \r\n\r\nThis is what he suggested that saved us close to 3000$!\r\n\r\nHe suggested that we first get the loan approved by bank/credit union of our choice and then go to a dealer for negotiating. He then suggested that we look for average price of the car that people pay through Kelly blue book or similar such service. \r\n\r\nWith this, he said, we could go to a dealer and negotiate. His suggestion was to negotiate with the first dealer to get his best offer and then speak to a few more dealers, now that we would have an idea about how much the dealers would be willing to sell the car for. \r\n\r\nFinally, when we would be satisfied with what the dealer is offering in terms of price and other things, we reveal that we already have the loan approved so we can directly get into the paper work.\r\n\r\nThe lesson I got: We can learn from anyone, because the world is a teacher!\r\n\r\nThanks you so much Howard!','2017-09-18 01:54:04','2017-09-18 01:54:04'),(55,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',48,'SaladBox','SoFASaladbox@gmail.com','thankingli-images/1/b9cdc29e7630a5eddde1d5f4477921ac.jpeg','For respecting the fact that some people are vegetarian','I have been to many restaurants, most of them serving both vegetarian and non-vegetarian food. \r\n\r\n In many cases I see, restaurants, especially the fast-food types, don’t bother to even change the gloves while making something vegetarian. While it may be ok with many people, it is definitely not ok with many others and me being a vegetarian understand this concern. Whats more disheartening is the callous attitude of the restaurants toward this concern people have.\r\n\r\nThis wasn’t the case with SaladBox. When the manager, Nila, heard my order “quinoa salad without chicken” she just looked at me without really saying anything and then when my wife ordered another vegetarian salad she instantly knew that we were vegetarian. She turned toward me and my wife and asked us if we were vegetarians to confirm and then with a smile on her face said “I just wanted to confirm so I make sure that everything in your order is vegetarian”.\r\n\r\nWhen our order was ready, she reiterated “it’s 100% vegetarian” again with a smile.\r\n\r\nThis is not about the food being 100% vegetarian, but about the respect this manager had for the choice some people make. The point is: she was sensitive!\r\n\r\nThanks a lot Nila from SaladBox for respecting people’s choice; This is highly appreciated.\r\n\r\nAnd my quinoa salad was great!!','2017-09-25 02:27:46','2017-10-03 16:51:28'),(56,2,'Kailash Suresh',0,'Shiri -Google launchpad','shiris@google.com','thankingli-images/2/35d049e13d45d41bf491a96ac6e1b55d.jpeg','Thank you for all the informative meet ups at google launchpad','I have been visiting 301 Howard - google launchpad for close to 10 months now and the meet ups there never seem to disappoint. They have some of the most informative sessions out there. Highly recommend you to check it out. I finally met the person behind Google launchpad. So wanted to leave a thank note to you!\r\nThanks you Shiri! Thank you Google launchpad!','2017-10-04 06:07:18','2017-10-04 06:07:18'),(57,1,'Madhu Prabhakara',50,'Thank you Lance @Romanos','1346@macgrill.com','thankingli-images/1/9f0a945b5d8787ae1655cc8619c3edfa.jpeg','For going above and beyond','My wife and I went to Romanos macaroni grill. As usual my wife ordered \"chicken under the brick\", her favourite dish at this restaurant. We were told it\'s not available. \r\n\r\nObviously my wife was disappointed and ordered something else. We had our dinner and came back home.\r\n\r\nA few days later we got a call from the restaurant, it was the manager(Lance). It was a random call just to get to know our experience. \r\n\r\nMy wife said what exactly happened the last time we went. Lance, the manager not only apologized but also gave my wife a coupon that allowed her to order \"chicken under the brick\" on the house. \r\n\r\nWe went there again and this time the dish was available. My wife was happy.\r\n\r\nHere is the best part, Lance got to know we visited again and immediately came to us and spoke to us for a few minutes making sure we were ok and apologized  again. \r\n\r\nHonestly, we\'d be ok even if we had not got the free \"chicken under the brick\", we\'d be ok even if we hadn\'t got that call.\r\n\r\nThis gesture was simply above and beyond what we generally expect.\r\n\r\nThanks a lot Lance, you truly taught us how we could  be f*****g great at what we do!','2017-10-07 03:36:17','2017-10-07 04:16:54');
